d of the eighth and seventh centuries B.C.E., while the notes present the range and possible meanings of important Greek terms and references in the poem and highlight areas of ambiguity in our understanding of Works and Days.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgriculturexPoetryxGreecexGreece. 0aDidactic poetry, GreekxTranslations into English. 4aAncient & Classical. 4aLiterary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aHesiod, Hesiod, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNeale, Walter C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTandy, David W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052020384640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091735440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520917354423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520917354/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles